HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) — Najibullah Zadran smashed a six off the second ball of the last over as Afghanistan beat host Zimbabwe by six wickets Saturday in the first of three Twenty20 internationals.Afghanistan needed eight runs off the final over, after Zimbabwe reached 159-8, and there was anticipation in the vocal small crowd at Harare Sports Club when the host’s star fast bowler Blessing Muzarabani was handed the ball for the last over to defend his team’s total.But Zadran collected two runs off the first ball before hitting Muzarabani over square leg for the maximum on the second delivery as Afghanistan reached 160-4 to win with four balls to spare.Earlier, Sikandar Raza top-scored for Zimbabwe with 45 in a measured innings.Afghanistan seamer Nijat Masood took 3-39 on his international debut.“It is the dream of every player to represent his country and to win a debut match,” Masood said. “I bowled in the good areas. That is how I was rewarded and took wickets.”ADVERTISEMENTOpeners Hazratullah Zazai (45) and Rahmanullah Gurbaz (33) gave Afghanistan a strong start in chase.Three of the Afghanistan wickets fell to the leg spin of Zimbabwe’s Ryan Burl.Afghanistan comes into the T20 matches after sweeping the host 3-0 in the one-day international series.___More AP cricket: https://apnews.com/hub/cricket and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports